{
  "texts": [
    "However, KiDS observations were not taken in the year 2000.",
    "Rather, the typical KiDS observation was taken around 2015-2016.",
    "As a result, the observed positions of stars in KiDS imaging are actually much more similar to the observed positions of Gaia stars at epoch J2016.The fact that KiDS is calibrated to J2000 epoch stars, but that KiDS images were taken around epoch J2016 (similar to Gaia) leads to an apparent systematic bias when performing a direct sky match between the KiDS DR5 catalogues and Gaia stars at their epoch J2016 positions: there appears to be a systematic bias in the two hemispheres, at the level of |∆RA| ∼ 0.",
    "′′ 1, which has different sign in the northern and the southern hemispheres.",
    "This can be seen in A170, page 47 of 54 Wright, A. H., et al."
  ]
}